    "description": "We at Juspay South Asia Partners are looking for an experienced Credit Analyst based out of Kochi. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Juspay South Asia Partners:\nJuspay South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kochi, Kerala, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Juspay South Asia Partners!",
